== History ==
Basadi ba pele bao maina a bone a itseweng archaeology a akaretsa:
* Neithhotep (c. 3200 BCE), mosadi wa Narmer le kgosigadi wa ntlha wa Egepeta ya kgale [ancient Egypt].<ref>Aidan Dodson & Dyan Hilton (2004). </ref><ref>J. Tyldesley, ''Chronicle of the Queens of Egypt'', 2006, Thames & Hudson.</ref>
* Merneith (c. 3000 BCE), consort and regent ya Egepeta ya kgale metlheng ysdinasti ya ntlha [first dynasty]. E ka be e ne e le mmusisi wa Egepeta ka bo ena. <ref name="books.google.co.uk"><cite class="citation book">Wilkinson, Toby A.H. (2001). </cite></ref><ref>Aidan Dodson & Dyan Hilton (2004). </ref>
* Merit-Ptah (c. 2700 BCE), le ena o dutse kwa Egepeta gape ke mosadi wa pele wa go nna ngaka [physician] le wa tsa matlhale [scientist].<ref>[http://www.astr.ua.edu/4000WS/MERIT_PTAH.html Merit-Ptah] at the University of Alabama.</ref>
* Peseshet (c. 2600 BCE), ke ngaka [physician] kwa Ancient Egypt.<ref>Plinio Prioreschi, ''A History of Medicine'', Horatius Press 1996, p. 334.</ref><ref>Lois N. Magner, ''A History of Medicine'', Marcel Dekker 1992, p. 28.</ref>
* Puabi (c. 2600 BCE), kgotsa Shubad – kgosigadi ya kwa Ur yoo lebitla la gagwe le fitlhetsweng le na le diartifacts tsa tlhwatlhwa e e kwa godimo. Dikgosigadi dingwe tsa kwa Ur tse di itseweng tsa pele ga Sargonic (bahumagadi ba segosi) ba akaretsa Ashusikildigir, Ninbanda, le Gansamannu.<ref><cite class="citation book">Elisabeth Meier Tetlow (2004). </cite></ref>
* Kugbau (''circa'' 2,500 BCE), a taverness from Kish chosen by the Nippur priesthood to become hegemonic ruler of Sumer, and in later ages deified as "Kubaba"
* Tashlultum (c. 2400 BCE), Akkadian kgosigadi, mosadi wa Sargon of Akkad gape e le mmagwe Enheduanna.<ref><cite class="citation book">Elisabeth Meier Tetlow (2004). </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation book">Michael Roaf (1992). </cite></ref>
* Baranamtarra (c. 2384 BCE), prominent and influential queen of Lugalanda of Lagash. Dikgosigadi dingwe tse di itseweng tsa pele ga-Sargonic tsa dynasty ya ntlha ya Lagash di akaretsa Menbara-abzu, Ashume'eren, Ninkhilisug, Dimtur, le Shagshag, mme maina a a mmalwa a dikhumagatsana dingwe le one a a itsege. <br>
* Enheduanna (c. 2285 BCE),<ref><cite class="citation web">Samuel Kurinsky. </cite></ref><ref><cite class="citation web">Jennifer Bergman (19 July 2001). </cite></ref> moprisitagadi o mogolo [high priestess] wa tempele ya modimo wa Ngwedi [ Moon God] kwa  Sumerian motsemogolong wa Ur mme ka gongwe e le mmoki wa ntlha yo a itsegeng ebile e le mokwadi wa ntlha wa bong bongwe le bongwe.<ref><cite class="citation book">J. M. Adovasio, Olga Soffer, Jake Page (2007). </cite></ref>

